---
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import '../../styles/main.css';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Site Design Updates | Hacker1 v1.0</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Latest updates, improvements, and announcements for the Site Design section." />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}favicon.svg`} />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Century+Schoolbook&family=Roboto:wght@400;500&family=EB+Garamond:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  </head>
  <body class="dark-mode site-design-background">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb">
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}`}>Home</a> → 
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}site-design`}>Site Design</a> → 
        Updates
      </nav>
      
      <h1>Site Design Updates</h1>
      
      <div class="content-section implementation-background">
        <h2>Recent Updates</h2>
        <p>
          "See, I am doing a new thing! Now it springs up; do you not perceive it?" - Isaiah 43:19
        </p>
        
        <div class="updates-timeline">
          <div class="update-item">
            <div class="update-date">July 2025</div>
            <div class="update-content">
              <h4>Site Design Resources Page Added</h4>
              <p>Comprehensive collection of design tools, principles, and learning resources now available. Includes spiritual perspectives on design thinking and user experience.</p>
              <div class="update-tags">
                <span class="tag">Resources</span>
                <span class="tag">Documentation</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="update-item">
            <div class="update-date">July 2025</div>
            <div class="update-content">
              <h4>Chapter 1 Content Enhanced</h4>
              <p>Expanded the foundation principles section with more detailed coverage of accessibility, performance, and biblical design wisdom.</p>
              <div class="update-tags">
                <span class="tag">Content</span>
                <span class="tag">Chapter 1</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="update-item">
            <div class="update-date">June 2025</div>
            <div class="update-content">
              <h4>Navigation Improvements</h4>
              <p>Added floating bottom navbar across all pages for consistent navigation. Improved breadcrumb navigation and chapter linking.</p>
              <div class="update-tags">
                <span class="tag">UI/UX</span>
                <span class="tag">Navigation</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-section solution-background">
        <h2>Planned Improvements</h2>
        <p>
          "For I know the plans I have for you," declares the Lord, "plans to prosper you 
          and not to harm you, to give you hope and a future." - Jeremiah 29:11
        </p>
        
        <div class="planned-features">
          <div class="feature-item">
            <h4>Interactive Design Examples</h4>
            <p>Adding live, interactive examples of design principles in action. Users will be able to experiment with layouts, colors, and typography in real-time.</p>
            <div class="status-badge planned">Planned</div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="feature-item">
            <h4>Design Pattern Library</h4>
            <p>Comprehensive library of reusable design patterns and components with spiritual themes and accessibility best practices.</p>
            <div class="status-badge in-progress">In Progress</div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="feature-item">
            <h4>Biblical Design Case Studies</h4>
            <p>Detailed analysis of how biblical principles can be applied to modern web design challenges and user experience decisions.</p>
            <div class="status-badge planned">Planned</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-section experimental-background">
        <h2>Community Feedback</h2>
        <p>
          "As iron sharpens iron, so one person sharpens another." - Proverbs 27:17
        </p>
        
        <div class="feedback-section">
          <div class="feedback-item">
            <h4>Accessibility Focus Appreciated</h4>
            <p>"The emphasis on accessibility as a moral imperative really resonates. It's refreshing to see spiritual values applied to technical design."</p>
            <cite>— Design Community Member</cite>
          </div>
          
          <div class="feedback-item">
            <h4>Scripture Integration Meaningful</h4>
            <p>"The way biblical principles are woven throughout the design guidance helps me think about my work differently."</p>
            <cite>— UX Designer</cite>
          </div>
          
          <div class="feedback-item">
            <h4>Request for More Examples</h4>
            <p>"Would love to see more practical examples showing these principles in action on real websites."</p>
            <cite>— Web Developer</cite>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-section implementation-background">
        <h2>Contributing</h2>
        <p>
          "Each of you should use whatever gift you have to serve others, as faithful stewards 
          of God's grace in its various forms." - 1 Peter 4:10
        </p>
        
        <div class="contribute-options">
          <div class="contribute-item">
            <h4>Share Your Experience</h4>
            <p>Have you applied these design principles in your work? We'd love to hear about your experiences and learn from your insights.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="contribute-item">
            <h4>Suggest Resources</h4>
            <p>Know of tools, articles, or resources that align with our design philosophy? Help us build a better resource collection.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="contribute-item">
            <h4>Request Topics</h4>
            <p>What design topics would you like to see covered? Your requests help guide our content development priorities.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="navigation-section">
        <div class="nav-buttons">
          <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}site-design/resources`} class="button is-light">← View Resources</a>
          <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}site-design`} class="button is-primary">Back to Site Design →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Add the custom floating bottom navbar -->
    <Navbar />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  .container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: white;
  }

  h1 {
    color: #e8d5b7;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #8b7355;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .content-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    color: #f0f0f0;
  }

  .content-section h2 {
    color: #e8d5b7;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #8b7355;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .content-section h4 {
    color: #d4af37;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .updates-timeline {
    display: grid;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .update-item {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 120px 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border-left: 3px solid #8b7355;
  }

  .update-date {
    color: #d4af37;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .update-tags {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .tag {
    background: rgba(212, 175, 55, 0.2);
    color: #d4af37;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }

  .planned-features {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .feature-item {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border-left: 3px solid #5a7a5a;
    position: relative;
  }

  .status-badge {
    position: absolute;
    top: 1rem;
    right: 1rem;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .status-badge.planned {
    background: rgba(138, 90, 90, 0.3);
    color: #c29999;
    border: 1px solid #8a5a5a;
  }

  .status-badge.in-progress {
    background: rgba(212, 175, 55, 0.3);
    color: #d4af37;
    border: 1px solid #d4af37;
  }

  .feedback-section {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .feedback-item {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border-left: 3px solid #7a5a7a;
  }

  .feedback-item cite {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    opacity: 0.8;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .contribute-options {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .contribute-item {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border-left: 3px solid #8b7355;
  }

  .navigation-section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
  }

  .nav-buttons {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .button {
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .button.is-light {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    color: #f0f0f0;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
  }

  .button.is-light:hover {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
  }

  .button.is-primary {
    background: #8b7355;
    color: white;
    border: 1px solid #8b7355;
  }

  .button.is-primary:hover {
    background: #a0845f;
  }

  /* Add padding to body to prevent navbar overlap */
  body {
    padding-bottom: 100px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .nav-buttons {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
    
    .container {
      padding: 1rem;
    }

    .update-item {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .contribute-options {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
